WHEREAS, with continued support for SGAC's mission, its members can continue their
tireless work advocating for sound policy decisions, transparency, and good governance and
enhancing the relationship between state and local governments, businesses, and communities;
and
WHEREAS, the fiftieth anniversary of SGAC represents a milestone of achievement and
service in its ongoing commitment to excellence in government affairs; and
WHEREAS, it is most appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should
specially recognize the State Government Affairs Council on this historic occasion; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby honor and commend the State
Government Affairs Council on the occasion of its fiftieth anniversary, commending its
membership, both past and present, on five decades of service to the State of Tennessee and
acknowledging its enduring influence on the State's government affairs landscape.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
